After graduating, I immediately went to Georgia Military College where I obtained my Associates degree in Criminal Justice and in 2012, I graduated from Valdosta State University with my Bachelors in Criminal Justice while making the Dean's List both years. After moving to Tennessee, I started working for Rainforest Cafe, where I later decided to move to Dave and Busters - it is here that I have quickly moved within the company. I have the roll of Traveling Certified Trainer where I recently opened a new store in Edina, Minnesota. I am excited to see where my career takes me, the possibilities are endless.

name: Hannah D'Arcy-Burt
about: I am a highly skilled Occupational Therapist with vast experience in the assessment and treatment of individuals with a variety of physical health conditions. I am passionate about the Occupational Therapy profession working pro-actively to support individuals to reach their true potential. I am forward thinking and ambitious, actively pursuing opportunities to develop clinical skills and engage in reflective practice. I uses advanced clinical reasoning skills to assess my client's occupational identity and competence enabling me to identify occupational deprivation and develop holistic treatments to suit the needs of the individual. I made the leap into independent practice due to my desire, passion and drive to provide high quality, person centred therapy to my clients. I primarily work with paediatric client's developing their ability to engage in activities of daily living. I enjoy working to improve sensory and motor skill impairments. I have significant experience in housing and adaptations including vehicle adaptations.

name: Hannah Burt
position: Master of Real Estate Graduate Student at Texas A&M University
about: As a recent Texas A&M University graduate (December 2024) with a Bachelor of Science in Agribusiness and a minor in Economics, I have specialized in financially based decision-making, economic analysis, and sustainable land use strategies. These skills, paired with my current pursuit of a Master of Real Estate (MRE) from Mays Business School at Texas A&M, position me to make a meaningful impact in the commercial real estate industry. My journey has been shaped by academic achievements, leadership roles, and hands-on experiences. Highlights include: ‚Ä¢ Active involvement in the MSC Abbott Family Leadership Conference and Texas A&M‚Äôs Student Government Association, where I developed strong leadership and collaborative skills. ‚Ä¢ Volunteering with Restoration Church Bryan and affiliated ministries, where I‚Äôve cultivated high moral standards and a passion for helping others. ‚Ä¢ Gaining adaptability and critical thinking skills through work experiences that span office settings and outdoor environments. I love the outdoors, deepening my love for the land. From the mountains of Northern New Mexico to the woods and lakes of the Brazos valley, I have spent many hours casting lines and calling gamebirds. I am an avid hunter, fly fisherman, and outdoorsman. My ideal weekend would be spent sleeping beneath the stars and exploring God‚Äôs green earth. I‚Äôm eager to learn from industry professionals and to broaden my understanding of commercial real estate. If you are looking for a fresh perspective, undeterred by hard work and passionate about land, let‚Äôs connect! I‚Äôd love to hear your story and explore how we can collaborate.

name: Hannah McCarthy
position: Sparking curiosity, one molecule at a time! üß™ | National Education & Outreach Coordinator at The Royal Australian Chemical Institute
about: At the helm of national education and outreach for The Royal Australian Chemical Institute, my focus is on cultivating a deeper public understanding of chemistry through inventive event planning and impactful project/initiative coordination. The role leverages my robust background in media and communications, ensuring that complex scientific concepts are translated into engaging experiences. With extensive expertise in project management, I oversee educational initiatives from conception through to delivery. This includes securing funding, coordinating resources, and leading teams to achieve our goals. My projects aim to inspire and educate the next generation of chemists by providing hands-on, inquiry-based learning opportunities. Through strategic partnerships, innovative programming, and a commitment to inclusivity, I strive to make chemistry education impactful and widely accessible.

name: Hannah Burt
about: Through my leadership roles in retail, I have seen the power of effective marketing through many channels. I ask the right questions for marketing research that drives results. I see evangelism as a form of marketing with eternal value, and have worked in research for donor ministries for multiple nonprofit organizations.
